    "These deep learning-based techniques face several challenges in their application in the agricultural sector.",
    "Usually, deep learning methods need an extensive amount of data to learn the pattern.",
    "However, the rapid spoilage of agricultural samples limits the avail-Fig. 4 Ground-truth and reconstructed a images and b spectra of eggs by Ahmed et al. (2024d) ability of data necessary for these techniques.",
    "Furthermore, these methods are sensitive to environmental conditions like light and weather, which can lead to inconsistencies in the reconstructed signals (Arad and Ben-Shahar 2016; Mu et al. 2024).",
    "In complex scenarios, accurately representing the diversity and variability of the scene can be challenging for hyperspectral image reconstruction."
  ]
